<container xmlns="https://open.law/schemas/library" xmlns:cache="https://open.law/schemas/cache" xmlns:citations="https://open.law/schemas/citations" xmlns:macro="https://open.law/schemas/macro" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:codified="https://open.law/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://open.law/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <prefix>Chapter</prefix>
  <num>06</num>
  <heading>Civil Citations</heading>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Scope.</heading>
    <text>Unless otherwise indicated, the fines under <cite path="|09|08|06|.02">Regulation .02 of this chapter</cite> apply for civil citations issued by the Commission under <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gbr|8-620">Business Regulation Article, §8-620(c)(1), Annotated Code of Maryland</cite>.</text>
    <annotations/>
  </section>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.02</num>
    <heading>Violation.</heading>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>Failure to include the name or license number in an advertisement:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $100; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $300.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>Publishing a false, misleading, or deceptive advertisement:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $300; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>C.</num>
      <text>Failure to display the license number on vehicle:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $100; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $300.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>D.</num>
      <text>Perform or sell a home improvement with or through an unlicensed person:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $5,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>E.</num>
      <text>Failure of a salesperson to account for, or remit, a payment received:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $3,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>F.</num>
      <text>Failure of a contractor to notify Commission of the hiring or termination of a salesperson:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>G.</num>
      <text>Failure of a contractor to notify the Commission within 10 days of a change of ownership, management, address, or trade name:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>H.</num>
      <text>Violation of a building law of the State or a political subdivision, a safety or labor law of the State, the Maryland Workers’ Compensation Act, or the lead paint accreditation requirement under <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gen|6-1002">Environment Article, §6-1002, Annotated Code of Maryland</cite>:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>I.</num>
      <text>Acting as a contractor or selling a home improvement under a name other than that under which the person is licensed:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>J.</num>
      <text>Failure to have a written and legible contract:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>K.</num>
      <text>Failure to have on a contract, the name, address, telephone number, and license number of the contractor:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>L.</num>
      <text>Failure to have on a contract a clear description of each document that it incorporates:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>M.</num>
      <text>Failure to have a contract signed by each party:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>N.</num>
      <text>Failure to have on a contract the approximate start and completion dates:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>O.</num>
      <text>Failure to have on a contract notice about the Commission and telephone number of the Commission:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>P.</num>
      <text>Failure to have on a contract a written notice as required whenever payment is secured by an interest in real estate:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>Q.</num>
      <text>Failure to have the notice required under <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gbr|8-501">Business Regulation Article, §8-501(c)(2), Annotated Code of Maryland</cite>, initialed by owner:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $2,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>R.</num>
      <text>Failure to provide a copy of a contract to an owner:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>S.</num>
      <text>Failure to have on a contract including a mandatory arbitration clause the notice required under <cite path="09.08.01.25|A.">COMAR 09.08.01.25A</cite>:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>T.</num>
      <text>Failure to obtain owner’s initials on a mandatory arbitration clause in a contract:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $2,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>U.</num>
      <text>Demand or receive any payment before contract is signed:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>V.</num>
      <text>Receipt of more than 1/3 deposit at the time of contract signing:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>W.</num>
      <text>Failure to comply with an order or requirement of Commission:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>X.</num>
      <text>Offering to act as a contractor without a license from the Commission:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $3,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>Y.</num>
      <text>Acting as a contractor without a license from the Commission:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $5,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>Z.</num>
      <text>. Reserved.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>AA.</num>
      <text>Offering to sell a home improvement without a license from the Commission:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $500; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $1,500.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>BB.</num>
      <text>Selling a home improvement without a license from the Commission:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $1,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $3,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>CC.</num>
      <text>Accepting a completion certificate with knowledge that the document is false:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation — $2,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation — $5,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>DD.</num>
      <text>Failure to maintain a surety bond that a licensee is required to hold to satisfy financial solvency requirements under <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gbr|8-305">Business Regulation Article, §8-305, Annotated Code of Maryland</cite>:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>First violation—$2,000; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Second or subsequent violation—$5,000.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <annotations/>
  </section>
